From: rxm7706 <rxm7706@protonmail.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] vector_of_kll: drop const on k_/d_ so operator= compiles

The copy- and move-assignment operators of vector_of_kll_sketches
assign to the members k_ and d_, which are declared `const uint32_t`.
Assigning to a const member is ill-formed C++ and GCC 14 (the current
conda-forge default compiler) rejects it as a hard error:

    src/vector_of_kll.cpp:146:6: error: assignment of read-only member
      'datasketches::vector_of_kll_sketches<T, C>::k_'

Drop the `const` qualifier from the two member declarations so the
existing assignment operators are well-formed. Semantics are unchanged
(the values are still set only in the constructor and in operator=).

Upstream bug present in 5.0.2 and still on main as of 2026-06-19.
TODO: drop this patch once upstream removes the const qualifiers.
---
 src/vector_of_kll.cpp | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/vector_of_kll.cpp b/src/vector_of_kll.cpp
--- a/src/vector_of_kll.cpp
+++ b/src/vector_of_kll.cpp
@@ -104,8 +104,8 @@
     template<typename TT>
     Array2D<TT> make_ndarray(size_t rows, size_t cols) const;

-    const uint32_t k_; // kll sketch k parameter
-    const uint32_t d_; // number of dimensions (here: sketches) to hold
+    uint32_t k_; // kll sketch k parameter
+    uint32_t d_; // number of dimensions (here: sketches) to hold
     std::vector<kll_sketch<T, C>> sketches_;
 };

